(\lambda)
y
F(y) = \int_0^y \lambda e^{-\lambda t} dt = 1 - e^{-\lambda y}.
F(y) - 1 = - e^{-\lambda y} \Rightarrow -\lambda y = \ln (1- F(y)) \Rightarrow y = F^{-1}(x) = -\ln(1-x)/\lambda.
